EU Referendum by numbers as polls close in the Brexit ballot

2016-06-23

Millions of voters braved torrential rain and floods to make sure they got to vote in the Brexit ballot.

Remain campaigners are “quietly optimistic” the historic vote is swinging their way.

A flurry of final polls all pointed to Britain wanting to stay in the European Union .

And following the end of the campaign Britain's political leaders are appealing for unity in the face of such division throughout the EU Referendum campaign.

Now the polls are closed and the count has begun, we take a look at the EU Referendum by numbers.

